# Read: 08 - More CSS Layout

Summary:

1.	Multiple sections in a page can be grouped together using <div> element.
2.	Normal flow is the default positioning for the browsers.
3.	We can use float property to move content to the left or right of the page. It is used to create multi-column layouts.
4.	Multiple CSS files can be contained in one page.
5.	Use of Grids help to create professional and flexible designs.
6.	CSS frameworks provide set of rules for common task.
7.	Pages can be fixed width or liquid (stretchy) layouts.



